text:
I once was entic’d to embark on a scheme;
A letter inform’d me that all would go to wreck;
But the paunchy old landlord came waddling up stairs,
With a noble bottle that banish’d my cares.

source_text:
I once was persuaded a venture to make;
A letter inform’d me that all was to wreck;
But the pursy old landlord just waddl’d upstairs,
With a glorious bottle that ended my cares.
